You can send all the slices at once or send one at a time and animate it onto the screen at the current time."}],"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout","role":"symbol","title":"ScrollLayout","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"AutoScroller"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"AutoScroller is a utility class to send a large known block of predfined text to the glasses to be smoothly scrolled."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is simlar to what is seen on a teleprompter or in movie credits.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This class was written using the ","type":"text"},{"code":"ScrollLayout","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" commands and is nothing more than a convience class."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Everything used this class can be written from the public SDK."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It scrolls the text much like a teleprompter would with basic commands to pause and resume the scrolling.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The duration (speed) of the scrolling can be modified while scrolling by seting the "},{"code":"duration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" property.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It can support any language that the font supports.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"If the content is not known up front, or subject to change, this is the utility class will not work (use "},{"code":"LiveText","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance instead).","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller","title":"ScrollLayout.AutoScroller"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK":{"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","title":"UltraliteSDK","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this SDK to easily send text and images to your Vuxix smart glasses."}],"role":"collection"}}}